The paper deals with graph edge-coloring problems, which are typically studied in the areas of discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), graph theory (cs.GT), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of abstraction and symmetry is a common technique in these areas, further supporting the likelihood of these sub-categories.
